</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
This species is provisionally included in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1814" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Campiglossa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="irrorata" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irrorata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">irrorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and was illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Agarwal, ML" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Insect Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" pagination="88 - 94" refId="B1" refString="Agarwal, ML, Grewal, JS, Kapoor, VC, Gupta, SK, Sharma, SK, 1989. Three new species of fruit flies (Diptera: Tephritidae) from India. Journal of Insect Science 2 (2): 88 - 94" title="Three new species of fruit flies (Diptera: Tephritidae) from India." volume="2" year="1989">Agarwal et al. (1989)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Kapoor, VC" journalOrPublisher="Invertebrate Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" refId="B13" refString="Kapoor, VC, 1993. Indian Fruit Flies (Insecta: Diptera: Tephritidae). International Science Publisher, New York, viii + 228 pp." title="Indian Fruit Flies (Insecta: Diptera: Tephritidae). International Science Publisher, New York, viii + 228 pp." year="1993">Kapoor (1993)</bibRefCitation>
. It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. cribellata" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="cribellata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">C. cribellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the reduced hyaline wing markings (particularly in the pterostigma and cell r1) and the more elongate wing. This species is known only from the type locality. The holotype, deposited in NPC, could not be traced and might have been lost or misplaced; hence, a diagnosis and redescription are not included here. Its unusual wing shape suggests that placement in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Campiglossa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Campiglossa" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Campiglossa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
requires confirmation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
